5. Towards medical policy: Health and society
Today we easily accept the claim that health is a community concern. This awareness,
however, has not always characterized European culture. The issue of health in society
is a history of increasing state intervention in matters of public health, not only in
maintaining the cleanliness in towns, ordering quarantines during epidemics, drain-
ing and sewage, but also in drafting building codes, laws to protect food and water
supplies, rules about traffic, and fire regulations. In extraordinary times, additional
```
