3.3 Discourse form
```
The length of the texts is varied, and most texts (10 out of 15) are included in toto
```
in the corpus. The shorter texts represent a different style of writing, including
```
advertisements and How to plant tobacco (1615), which is written in an instruc-
```
tive style.
Unlike speciric DisEasEzs, texts On SPECIFIC THERAPEUTIC SUBSTANCES in gen-
eral go straight to the point and are practice-oriented, without long discussions on the
nature of the remedies. The types of potions, lotions, remedies, etc., are often structur-
ally organized into their own paragraphs and written in a handbook-like style where
```
the information needed is conveniently presented for the reader (see Wear 2000: 82
```
```
for data retrieval):
