```
```
author of Popular pill, 1674), but quacks and enterpreneurs. The commercial aspect
```
```
is evident in the language, especially in the extensive use of hyperbole (see Ratia
```
```
and Suhr forthcoming). For example, Anthony Daffy referred to his Elixir salutis
