Although most of the recipe collections and texts on materia medica follow this
kind of segmented structure consisting of formulaic recipes, there are some texts that
weave their remedies into a more narrative framework. For example, the Approved
medicines of Richard Elkes recounts remedies supposedly imparted to the author by an
“old Souldier in Ireland about forty years since, which became a Physitian there”:
```
