1. Chronological coverage
Like recipe collections and materia medica, regimens and health guides have a strong
tradition in vernacular writing dating back to the Middle Ages, and the tradition con-
tinued throughout the early modern period. The entire period of EMEMT is covered
evenly. Although there are slightly more texts from the sixteenth century than from
the seventeenth, there are no significant gaps in the timeline.
