```
subject matter of the articles and their degree of sophistication. Medical issues were
high among the concerns of the fellows of the society. Medical practitioners formed
```
the largest and most active occupational group within the society (Porter 1989: 272),
```
and roughly a tenth of the fellows were also members of the College of Physicians
```
(Hall 1971: 112)?
