If the box “Case-sensitive search” is ticked, EMEMT Presenter pays close atten-
tion to the case of each letter in the word. A search for “the” would thus not return
instances of “The” or “THE”. Note that the editors of the EMEMT corpus have faith-
fully preserved the original orthography, and that upper case lettering was used much
more frequently in early modern printing than today. It is generally best to keep this
control unticked,
“Use delimiters with finds” controls the way punctuation and other non-letter
characters are handled by EMEMT Presenter. It is advised to leave this control to the
