4-4 Collocations and advanced search
Sometimes you may be interested in seeing what words occur close to a particular
word at an unusually high frequency. Such words are called collocates - from co +
location — in corpus linguistics. In EMEMT Presenter, “Collocation analysis” can be
carried out after a search. Likewise, you may be interested in searching for more
complex syntactical or morphological structures by employing two search terms
and defining the relationship between them. “Advanced search” allows much more
control over the way a search is conducted. Detailed instruction on both “Colloca-
tions” and “Advanced search” functions can be found in the documentation within
EMEMT Presenter.
