8.5 Editorial notes
In addition to the transcription of the original text, the corpus texts contain some.
editorial annotations added by the corpus compilers to describe the treatment of the
original text in the corpus. Based on their contents, these comments can be divided
into two types: formal notes and descriptive comments. All of these editorial notes and
comments are set off from the text itself by enclosing them within tags consisting of
opening and closing square brackets and caret symbols.
